$interpreted: Announcer: Ladies and gentlemen, welcome to the Oasis Sports Day! Now, without further ado, let's welcome our teams!!
Announcer: First up, it's our reigning champs—The Rampaging Apes!
Announcer: And just listen to that applause, ladies and gentlemen!
Announcer: Next, it's our team of cuties—The 24-Karat Kittens!
Announcer: Watch out, these kittens have their claws out and they're ready to strike!
Announcer: Next up it's the dodgeball pioneers, the lusciously fiesty... Lupine Ladies!!
Announcer: Can't wait to see what they bring to the dodgeball event this year, ladies and gentlemen!
Announcer: Now, last and quite possibly least, ladies and gentlemen, please welcome our perennial underdogs—The Glory of the Oasis!
Kittyeyes: Oh man, no fanfare at all...
Announcer: Well, now that we've introduced our teams, let's get right into the first event--the opening dance!
Announcer: Let's see who The Rampaging Apes selected as their contestant!
Monkey Boy: Didn't think you chumps would end up findin' anybody. But, ain't that one of those tourists from the other day?
Monkey Boy: Hah, that's a laugh! Talk about desperate, need help from tourists just to get your foot in the door!
Kittyeyes: Man this guy's pissing me off...
Team Captain: Yeah, yeah, laugh it up while you still can. You're going down.
Monkey Boy: Wow, such confidence all of a sudden! Alright, then, how about a bet? If you lose, then your whole team belongs to me from now on!
Team Captain: What?
Monkey Boy: But if you win, then I'll disband the Rampaging Apes and skip town... for good.
Diana: Don't worry, we're well prepared. We can win.
Team Captain: Ah... Fine, I accept your bet!
Monkey Boy: Bwaha, perfect! The apes can never have too many members!
Announcer: And now let's see the Glory of the Oasis' contestant~
Kittyeyes: That's my cue.
Diana: You can do it, Kittyeyes.
Kittyeyes: Leave it to me~
Kittyeyes: (Oh man, I'm starting to get butterflies...)
Kittyeyes: Ohh~ kay~!!
Kittyeyes: Hey~~~ Ha~~~!!
Announcer: Wow, Kittyeyes' performance was incredible! I don't think I've ever seen a dance that good!
Announcer: Well, then, what do our judges think~?
Announcer: Five stars! Amazing, both the Rampaging Apes and Glory of the Oasis get a full five stars!!
Kittyeyes: Yess!!
Diana: Good job, Kittyeyes!
Kittyeyes: Heh~ It was nothin'.
Announcer: Well then, while the excitement is high, let's move onto the dodgeball event!
Kittyeyes: That's you, Nolva!
Nolva: Alright, I'll do my best.
Announcer: Round 1, Glory of the Oasis versus the Lupine Ladies! Ready... start!
Nolva: (Oh no... I'm getting sleepy...)
Lupine Lady: She's wide open!
Announcer: Whoa... what was that!? In the blink of an eye...!! That's a win for Nolva, and the Glory of the Oasis!!
Kittyeyes: Nice! Let's keep this roll going!
Announcer: Currently, the Rampaging Apes have an advantage. It's up to Nolva to turn the tides back into her team's favor!
Announcer: She did it! Nolva took back the lead... Glory of the Oasis wins!!
Monkey Boy: Hold on, I object!
Diana: Huh?
Monkey Boy: Glory of the Oasis cheated! Their win doesn't count!!
Kittyeyes: What the heck are you talking about!?
Monkey Boy: Nolva wasn't even awake the whole time, that's what the heck I'm talkin' about!!
Monkey Boy: According to the rules, contestants have to be fully conscious, or they're disqualified!
Team Captain: What nonsense! You're grasping at straws, monkey boy!
Kittyeyes: Nolva's just kind of a special case, that's all...
Monkey Boy: I don't care how special she is, rules are rules!!
Diana: Damn...!!
Judge: It's written down in black and white... they are the rules.
Judge: And so, the judges rule that in response to Glory of the Oasis' Nolva violating the rules, the dodgeball event's new winner is The Rampaging Apes.
Kittyeyes: What the... that's not fair!!
Diana: Just don't fight it, Kittyeyes. If you do, they might kick us out of the whole competition.
Nolva: Mngh... competition... why's everyone looking so serious?
Kittyeyes: Nolva...
Nolva: I'm sorry, it's all my fault...
Diana: It's not your fault.
Diana: I was too naive, I didn't think the other team would stoop so low.
Team Captain: If we get 0 points this round, it means The Rampaging Apes are ahead 15 to 5... We're down by 10 points!
Jerome: Don't worry, I'll get them back.
Nolva: Jerome, I...
Jerome: Don't worry about it. We're a team, right? I'll pick up the slack in the water war event.
Kittyeyes: That's the spirit! You can do it, Jer! Flatten those stupid monkeys!
Jerome: Did you just call me... Jer?
Kittyeyes: Got a problem with that?
Jerome: Nope... no problem.
Announcer: Attention, attention, we have finished preparation for the water war event. All participants in the water war event, please head to the arena.
Jerome: Well, then, wish me luck.
Monkey Boy: Down by 10 points and still haven't given up, huh? Bwahaha, if you can really make those points up, I'll eat a banana upside down!
Announcer: On your marks~ Get set~~ Gooo!!!
Announcer: Incredible, folks! In all my years, I've never seen such a strong performance!
Announcer: Jerome takes one down... and another... and another!! Jerome's about to win this event single-handedly!
Kittyeyes: Go Jer!! You can do it!!!
Nolva: Go Jerome!!
Announcer: I think Jerome really might do it! He could take this whole event!!
Announcer: Oh noo~ Too bad, Jerome's been taken out.
Announcer: Now, tallying up the points... The Rampaging Apes take 2 points, and the Glory of the Oasis get... 10 points! Incredible!
Jerome: I'm sorry, I couldn't get all of the points back.
Diana: Don't worry about that, you got so many! Look, it's 15 to 17 now!
Jerome: Wow, you're right.
Diana: Jerome!?
Jerome: Ah... it's nothing, I'm just a bit tired.
Kittyeyes: Don't scare me like that... Anyway, you did a good job, Jer. Didn't think you had it in you.
Team Captain: Today's events are finished, so Jerome should get some rest.
Diana: Okay.
Team Captain: Now... it might be too early to say this, but...
Team Captain: Thank you for giving our team hope once again. Tomorrow's the crab run, and I'm sure I'll take the victory there!
Diana: I'm looking forward to it, captain.
Monkey Boy: Pfft, scared the crap out of me.
Monkey Boy: What are you doing with that banana?
Rampaging Ape: Um, didn't you just said you'd eat a banana upside down if they caught up, boss?
Monkey Boy: Fuhgeddaboudit!!
Monkey Boy: Hmph~ Whatever, I have my ways to win...
Kittyeyes: Can't sleep again?
Diana: Not a wink... What about you? Training.
Kittyeyes: Yep! I'm working on my victory smile.
Diana: Your victory smile? Is that really something you have to practice?
Kittyeyes: Of course! Otherwise I might do some kind of weird grumpy face...
Diana: How are Jerome and Nolva?
Kittyeyes: They're still sleeping.
Diana: And the captain?
Kittyeyes: He's resting, too.
Diana: Good...
Panicked Athlete: Miss Diana, something's happened!
Panicked Athlete: The captain, he... he might not be able to compete tomorrow!!
